Business executives see the potential of the #metaverse to increase influence and profit margins. 95% of business executives believe the metaverse will benefit their sector within the next five to ten years, and 31% believe it would fundamentally alter how their sector functions.

The #metaverse is already being used by consumers
Customers have already arrived. 59% of customers prefer at least one metaverse encounter to its physical counterpart, demonstrating that consumers are enthusiastic about moving their lives into the metaverse.

This investor enthusiasm is fueled by a number of factors:

1. The tailwinds for the #metaverse are being powered by continual technical advancements throughout the necessary infrastructure.
2. Brand engagement and marketing are becoming more consumer-driven.

What is driving investment in the #metaverse?
More than $120 billion has already been invested in the metaverse this year by businesses, venture capitalists, and private equity firms, more than double the $57 billion invested throughout the entire previous year.

The research was conducted as a poll of more than 3,400 consumers and executives about the adoption of the metaverse, its potential, and how it will probably affect behavior. The industry leaders and creators of the #metaverse were invited too.

The value of the #metaverse might increase to $5 trillion by 2030. It identifies e-commerce as the largest economic force ($2.6 trillion), surpassing industries like gaming ($125 billion), virtual learning ($270 billion), and advertising ($206 billion).

According to a recent analysis by #McKinsey & Co., the value of the metaverse might increase to $5 trillion by 2030.
